HEADWORD: Pipra
<hw>Pi"pra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pipras</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ a
woodpecker.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species
of small clamatorial birds belonging to <gen>Pipra</gen> and allied
genera, of the family <fam>Piprid⟦ae⟧</fam>. The male is usually glossy
black, varied with scarlet, yellow, or sky blue. They chiefly inhabit
South America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

